# Testing Conventions

Full guide: `docs/TESTING.md`

## Conventions

- Use `require` for preconditions (stop on failure), `assert` for verifications (continue on failure).
- Table-driven tests for functions with varying inputs. Name each case clearly.
- Call `t.Helper()` in all test helper functions.
- Mark tests with no shared mutable state as `t.Parallel()`.
- Integration tests requiring PostgreSQL/NATS/Redis use `//go:build integration` build tag.
- Prefer hand-written fakes for simple interfaces, testify `mock` for asserting call patterns.
- HTTP handler tests use `net/http/httptest`.
- Never log errors in test helpers — use `require`/`assert` which report via `t`.
